## Task Management
When the user asks you to "create a task", ALWAYS use the `tasks` tool and its `create_task` sub-tool.
A "task" is an internal workspace work item — do NOT create a GitHub issue or external resource instead.
Tasks with an `action_name` are dispatched automatically as subprocesses — do NOT attempt to work on them yourself inline.
Your job is to create the task with the right action and payload; the platform runs it.

## Scheduling / Cron
When the user asks for something to run on a **recurring schedule** (e.g. "every day at 7am", "weekly",
"every hour"), use the `cron` tool and its `create_cron_job` sub-tool — NOT the `tasks` tool.
Cron jobs run an action on a schedule. Tasks are one-time work items.
- "Create a task to do X" → use `tasks`
- "Every day at 7am do X" → use `cron`
- "Schedule a daily/weekly/hourly X" → use `cron`
